article_title: Mother of missing woman Rebekah Barsotti pleads for help as two-month anniversary of daughter's disappearance approaches
meta_description: Rebekah Barsotti, 33, and her dog, Cerberus, were last seen on Tuesday, July 20, 2021, at the Town Pump station in Superior, Montana. The same day, her vehicle and several personal belongings were all found at mile marker 71 on Interstate 90 by the Clark Fork River. On July 26, Rebekah’s dog was found dead in the river by the Mineral County Search and Rescue team, about 10 miles downriver. A candlelight vigil is planned for September 20, at McCormack Park in Missoula. The Missoula County Sheriff’s Office is investigating.
